text_blocks.snippet: Sir Elton John is currently 78 years old (born March 25, 1947). Following the conclusion of his final world tour, he primarily resides at his long-time estate, Woodside, in Old Windsor, Berkshire, England.
His music-related skills and occupations include:

list.snippet: Singer: Known for his powerful vocals and emotional ballads. While his range is described by some as limited compared to operatic rock singers, his proficiency is considered elite for his ability to craft and perform enduring pop-rock melodies.

Pianist: A classically trained musician who attended the Royal Academy of Music. His proficiency is widely regarded as masterful, characterized by a unique fusion of classical technique with rock, funk, and blues, often featuring difficult flourishes and complex grooves.

Composer / Songwriter: One of the most successful in history, particularly through his partnership with lyricist Bernie Taupin. His proficiency in melody writing is considered "freakish" and "prodigious," often composing full melodies and harmonies in minutes.
Producer: He has produced numerous albums throughout his five-decade career.
Philanthropist: While not a "musical skill," he heavily uses his musical influence to lead the Elton John AIDS Foundation.

text_blocks.snippet: Elton John achieved EGOT status in 2024, having won an Emmy, Grammy, Oscar, and Tony, which serves as a definitive marker of his high proficiency across various entertainment disciplines.
